column30: This file was produced from running the standardized Hi-C pipeline on ChIA-PET fastq files. The processing may not be optimal as the Hi-C pipeline does not take the linkers used in ChIA-PET into account.

This file was produced from running the standardized Hi-C pipeline on ChIA-PET fastq files.  The processing may not be optimal as the Hi-C pipeline does not take the linkers used in ChIA-PET into account.

WARNING - Due to a bug in the version of cooler (0.8.3) used in the current 4DN standard Hi-C processing pipeline some pixels may occur mulitple times at a single resolution with different counts being reported for each occurence.  This duplication does not affect the higlass display of these files, howevver, downstream analyses using this file may encounter issues due to this pixel duplication.  The counts from the duplicate pixels can be aggregated to determine the correct count value at that location. If this issue is problematic for your needs you should consider regenerating the matrices from the merged pairs file of the associated dataset using a more recent version of cooler.  We are working to update the pipeline but do not yet have a predicted date for when this issue will be resolved., This file was produced from running the standardized Hi-C pipeline on ChIA-PET fastq files.  The processing may not be optimal as the Hi-C pipeline does not take the linkers used in ChIA-PET into account.

This merged pairs file was generated by running the pairs filtering step of the 4DN standard Hi-C pipeline using as input the individual pairs files produced by the experimental lab from the ChIA-PIPE analysis pipeline.

This contact matrix was generated by running the matrix aggregation and normalization step of the 4DN standard Hi-C pipeline on a merged pairs file.  The merged pairs file was produced by the pairs filtering step of the same pipeline using as input the individual pairs files produced by the experimental lab from the ChIA-PIPE analysis pipeline.

column2: IMPORTANT: As of October 15, 2020, you must include an access key in your cURL command for bulk downloads. You can configure the access key in your profile. If you do not already have an account, you can log in with your Google or GitHub credentials.
